==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recrudesce
<hw>Re`cru*desce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Recrudescent</er>.]</ety> <def>To be in a state of recrudescence;
esp., to come into renewed freshness, vigor, or activity; to
revive.</def></p>

<p><q>The general influence . . . which is liable every now and then to
<qex>recrudesce</qex> in his absence.</q> <rj><qau>Edmund
Gurney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recrudescency</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Recrudescence</ent>⟦br⟧
